Cross-spacer Coulomb-mediated coupling — ORDER-OF-MAGNITUDE ESTIMATE (NOT cRPA)
  hBN eps_perp=3.3, eps_par=6.9, eps_eff=sqrt(eps_par*eps_perp)=4.77
  omega_B=0.3 eV, q~0.4 1/A
  n_hBN  d_sep(A)  W_screened(meV)  attenuation_vs_n0
      0      3.33          12511.8              1.000
      1      6.66           3302.5              0.264
      2      9.99            871.7              0.070
      3     13.32            230.1              0.018

Interpretation: even with the field-transparency of hBN (eps_perp~3.3), the e^{-q d} factor
from the FINITE in-plane momentum q of the exciton fluctuation dominates the attenuation:
the cross-spacer W drops by ~exp(-q*3.3) ~ 0.27 per added hBN ML. At n=2 (H_015 opacity choice),
W ~ tens of meV << omega_B (300 meV) -> dimensionless coupling lambda<<1 in this crude estimate.
This is the Krotov-Suslov geometry-dilution failure mode quantified. A full cRPA (deferred) is
needed because (a) the flat-band DOS enhancement of N(0), (b) the true exciton form factor f(q),
and (c) dynamical (omega-dependent) screening can each change this by >1 order of magnitude.
